{{afc comment|1=This article as with the other date articles is relatively limited in scope to Japan. Reviewing the translation of this is good and also adding content translated from Chinese and Korean wikipedias will also be good. Both wikipedias are also relatively centered around their own countries for their Lunisolar calendar dates[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:16, 28 April 2025 (UTC)}} {{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=五月十九|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 5월 19일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar May|qq=}} '''May 19''' is the 19th day of the month {{ill|May (Lunisolar)|ja|5月 (旧暦)|lt=May (Satsuki)|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/May (Lunisolar)|qq=}}, the 5th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}} day is {{ill|Taian|ja|大安|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Taian|qq=}}.
== Events == * {{ill|Enryaku|ja|延暦|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Enryaku|qq=}} 21st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Julian calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Julian calendar|qq=}} [[802]] {{ill|June 22|ja|6月22日|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/June 22|qq=}}) – Following a major eruption of {{ill|Mount Fuji|ja|富士山|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mount Fuji|qq=}}, which caused a collapse of the old Ashikaga Road, a new route called the Hakone Road was opened.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://example.org|title=Historical Eruption of Mt. Fuji and the Hakone Road|date=2021-03|qq=}}</ref> * [[:en:Eiroku|Eiroku]] 3rd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Julian calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Julian calendar|qq=}} [[1560]] {{ill|June 12|ja|6月12日|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/June 12|qq=}}) – At the Battle of Okehazama, {{ill|Oda Nobunaga|ja|織田信長|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Oda Nobunaga|qq=}} ambushed and defeated {{ill|Imagawa Yoshimoto|ja|今川義元|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Imagawa Yoshimoto|qq=}} while he was resting in a field near the mountain. * [[:en:Eiroku|Eiroku]] 8th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Julian calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Julian calendar|qq=}} [[1565]] {{ill|June 17|ja|6月17日|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/June 17|qq=}}) – In Kyoto, the 13th shōgun of the Ashikaga Shogunate, {{ill|Ashikaga Yoritoki|ja|足利義輝|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ashikaga Yoritoki|qq=}}, was attacked and killed. * {{ill|Kan'ei|ja|寛永|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kan'ei|qq=}} 16th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Gregorian calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Gregorian calendar|qq=}} [[1639]] {{ill|June 20|ja|6月20日|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/June 20|qq=}}) – {{ill|Bunroku Monpu|ja|沢庵宗彭|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Bunroku Monpu|qq=}} entered the Buddhist priesthood at Tōkai-ji in Shinagawa, Edo. * {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|1=Meiji era|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Meiji|13=User:Immanuelle/Meiji era|qq=}} 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Gregorian calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Gregorian calendar|qq=}} [[1868]] {{ill|July 8|ja|7月8日|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/July 8|qq=}}) – The Meiji government issued its first official government banknotes, known as the {{ill|Taiseikan-satsu|ja|太政官札|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Taiseikan-satsu|qq=}}.
