== Events == * [[:en:Enryaku|Enryaku]] 21st year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[802]] [[:en:June 22|June 22]]) – Following a major eruption of [[:en:Mount Fuji|Mount Fuji]], which caused a collapse of the old Ashikaga Road, a new route called the Hakone Road was opened.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://example.org|title=Historical Eruption of Mt. Fuji and the Hakone Road|date=2021-03|qq=}}</ref> * [[:en:Eiroku|Eiroku]] 3rd year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[1560]] [[:en:June 12|June 12]]) – At the Battle of Okehazama, [[:en:Oda Nobunaga|Oda Nobunaga]] ambushed and defeated [[:en:Imagawa Yoshimoto|Imagawa Yoshimoto]] while he was resting in a field near the mountain. * [[:en:Eiroku|Eiroku]] 8th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[1565]] [[:en:June 17|June 17]]) – In Kyoto, the 13th shōgun of the Ashikaga Shogunate, [[:en:Ashikaga Yoshiteru|Ashikaga Yoritoki]], was attacked and killed. * [[:en:Kan'ei|Kan'ei]] 16th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1639]] [[:en:June 20|June 20]]) – [[:en:Takuan Sōhō|Bunroku Monpu]] entered the Buddhist priesthood at Tōkai-ji in Shinagawa, Edo. * [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] 1st year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1868]] [[:en:July 8|July 8]]) – The Meiji government issued its first official government banknotes, known as the {{ill|Taiseikan-satsu|ja|太政官札|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Taiseikan-satsu|qq=}}.
== Births == * [[:en:Man'en|Man'en]] 1st year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1860]] [[:en:July 7|July 7]]) – [[:en:Miyake Setsurei|Miyake Setsurō]], an intellectual (died [[1945]]).
== Deaths == * {{ill|Shitoku (Japan)|ja|至徳|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shitoku (Japan)|qq=}} 1st year / [[:en:Genchū|Genchū]] 1st year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[1384]] [[:en:June 8|June 8]]) – [[:en:Kan'ami|Kan'ami]], an actor of Noh (born [[1333]]). * [[:en:Eiroku|Eiroku]] 3rd year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[1560]] [[:en:June 12|June 12]]) – [[:en:Imagawa Yoshimoto|Imagawa Yoshimoto]], a military commander (born [[1519]]). * [[:en:Eiroku|Eiroku]] 8th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[1565]] [[:en:June 17|June 17]]) – [[:en:Ashikaga Yoshiteru|Ashikaga Yoritoki]], the 13th shōgun of the Ashikaga Shogunate (born [[1536]]). * [[:en:Keichō|Keichō]] 4th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1599]] [[:en:July 11|July 11]]) – [[:en:Chōsokabe Motochika|Chōsōga–be Motonaga]], a military commander (born [[1539]]). * [[:en:Shōhō|Shōhō]] 2nd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1645]] [[:en:June 13|June 13]]) – [[:en:Miyamoto Musashi|Miyamoto Musashi]], a renowned swordsman (born [[1584]]). * {{ill|Tenna|ja|天名|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenna|qq=}} 1st year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1681]] [[:en:July 4|July 4]]) – [[:en:Sakai Tadakiyo|Sakai Tadashige]], a Tairō of the Tokugawa shogunate (born [[1624]]). * [[:en:Kyōhō|Kyōhō]] 10th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1725]] [[:en:June 29|June 29]]) – [[:en:Arai Hakuseki|Arai Hakuseki]], a Rōjū and Confucian scholar (born [[1657]]). (Note: Some sources record May 10 for this event.) * [[:en:Bunkyū|Bunkyū]] 2nd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1862]] [[:en:June 16|June 16]]) – [[:en:Hidenoyama Raigorō|Shūnoyama Raigorō]], the 9th Yokozuna (born [[1808]]).
